{'id': 39569565, 'body': 'Hi Kerianys__1267! We really appreciate your feedback. Ovulation tests detect luteinizing hormone (LH), which suddenly, rapidly, and briefly increases right before you ovulate.

You can receive a negative result and still ovulate. If you have a sharp LH surge, for example, you may take one test before your surge is detectable by your kit and another test when your LH has already begun to decrease and is no longer detectable.

